<subSubSection pageNumber="519" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="519">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="519">Note:</emphasis>
Smith wrongly attributed the type choice to Merrill (
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="519">Interpret. Rumph. Herb. Ambe</emphasis>
.:195-196. 1917), who merely excluded the cited Rumphius element. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Smith’s">Smith's</normalizedToken>
own statement, however, typifies the name, though there appear to be doubts as to the identity of the type. Nicolson &amp; al. (
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="519">Interpret. Rheede Hort. Malab</emphasis>
.: 186. 1988) suggest it is probably identifiable as 
<taxonomicName authority="L." authorityName="Linnaeus" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Moraceae" genus="Ficus" higherTaxonomySource="IPNI" kingdom="Plantae" order="Urticales" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="microcarpa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="519">F. microcarpa</emphasis>
L.
</taxonomicName>
f.
</paragraph>
